The paper proposes a neural network model for system identification, which falls under the category of machine learning. The model is based on hinging hyperplanes and involves solving convex optimization problems, which suggests the paper may belong to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of the model in nonlinear system identification, which suggests it may belong to the sub-category of "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or "cs.SY" (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the model, which suggests it may belong to the sub-category of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) or "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms).
